se at 200 Garden Street. The NYMEX Center is located on North First Avenue in the World Financial Center. Even the Wall Street Journal is not on Wall Street itself. It\'s on 1211 Americas Street.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">History of the Wall Street Stock Exchange<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The Wall Street Wall dates back to the physical wall that was built when New York was still a Dutch colony. Then Governor Peter Stuyvesant ordered the construction of a 10-foot-tall wooden wall that would protect the Lower Peninsula from the British and Native Americans. It later became a bazaar on the street where merchants met under the now famous Patton Tree. In 1792 these dealers formalized the rules of the game and created the New York Stock Exchange.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Main take on Wall Street<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">\\u2022 Wall Street is the location in New York of the nation\'s largest financial firms.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">\\u2022 The New York Stock Exchange, where companies list securities to raise money, is also there.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">\\u2022 The two biggest financial crises that Wall Street created were the Great Depression of 1929 and the Great Depression of 2008.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">How the Wall Street Stock Exchange works<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Wall Street includes the stock market, the bond market, the commodity market, the futures market, and the forex market. The original purpose of the stock market was to raise money for companies to generate growth, generate profit, and create jobs. Stock trading has become so profitable in and of itself that trades are established for anything you can think of, and a lot of things you cannot imagine.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">What has changed on Wall Street? For one thing, the Glass-Steagall Act was repealed in 1999. This allowed any bank to use depositors \\u2019savings to invest in complex securities called derivatives. They based their value on different types of loans, including credit card debt, corporate bonds and mortgages.<\\/font><\\/p>\",\"ar\":\"<p>\\u0648\\u0648\\u0644 \\u0633\\u062a\\u0631\\u064a\\u062a \\u0647\\u064a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0631\\u0645\\u0632 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0631\\u0643\\u0632 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062c\\u063a\\u0631\\u0627\\u0641\\u064a \\u0644\\u0644\\u0631\\u0623\\u0633\\u0645\\u0627\\u0644\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0645\\u0631\\u064a\\u0643\\u064a\\u0629. \\u0631\\u0645\\u0632\\u064a\\u0627\\u064b\\u060c \\u062a\\u0634\\u064a\\u0631 \\u0648\\u0648\\u0644 \\u0633\\u062a\\u0631\\u064a\\u062a \\u0625\\u0644\\u0649 \\u062c\\u0645\\u064a\\u0639 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0628\\u0646\\u0648\\u0643 \\u0648\\u0635\\u0646\\u0627\\u062f\\u064a\\u0642 \\u0