style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">3. Derivatives such as futures and options<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">4. Reports issued by international energy agencies<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">5. The value of the US dollar is one of the factors affecting oil prices<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">What are the types of oil?<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">There are a number of types that are traded in the forex market, the most famous of which are:<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">West Texas Crude: It is a crude oil extracted in the United States of America, and is characterized by being light and low in density compared to the Arab Gulf oil and the oil produced by the countries of the OPEC group. For WTI, the group of symbols differs according to the trading platform, the most famous of which is (WTI, US OIL or OIL).<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Brent crude: It is also a crude oil, also described as being of low density, and is extracted and produced in the North Sea region. Brent crude is used to price two-thirds of oil production worldwide, the most common symbol for Brent crude on trading platforms is Brent.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">In fact, the two types are very similar and close in prices. At one point, the prices of West Texas crude oil were higher than Brent crude oil prices. Today, the picture has reversed, with Brent crude oil prices becoming slightly higher, but it must be noted that the factors that affect the prices of these two types are the same.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Oil technical analysis<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Technical analysis is used to forecast current and future oil prices, and technical analysis of oil is no different from technical analysis for other financial assets, as the same methods, tools and indicators are used, except that some traders and experts use special technical indicators to analyze oil prices.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The relationship between oil and the Canadian dollar<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Canada has large reserves of oil, estimated at 176 billion barrels of crude oil, and Canadian oil sands are the third oil reserves in the world. On the other hand, Canada is the first exporter of oil to the United States of America, in 2017 it was 99% of Canada\'s oil exports to America, which accounted for 43% of US oil imports.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Since oil is priced in US dollars, in the event of an increase in oil prices, we find that Canada gets more quantities of the US dollar through the sale of oil. In this case, the supply of the US dollar in the Canadian market increases and its price decreases against the Canadian dollar and vice versa. For this reason, we find that there is a positive positive relationship between the price of oil and the value of the Canadian dollar. When oil prices rise, the value of the Canadian dollar rises and vice versa.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Oil trading platforms<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The question about oil trading platforms is a common question among Arab traders, but in fact there are no special platforms for oil trading, as trading companies allow traders to invest in oil and various financial assets through the same platforms, the most famous and most popular of which is the MetaTrader 4 platform.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">How is oil traded online?<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Oil, like other assets traded in the forex market, depends on the system of speculation, meaning that the 