(3, 53, 53, '{\"en\":\"Dow Jones Index\",\"ar\":\"\\u0645\\u0624\\u0634\\u0631 \\u062f\\u0627\\u0648 \\u062c\\u0648\\u0646\\u0632\"}', 'post', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'publish', 0, NULL, NULL, '5f45ea1ea310675e2099e431.jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":\"Its full name is Dow Jones Industrial Average, hence its abbreviation DJIA, the Dow Jones 30 Index is a stock index of 30 major American companies. It is also called DJIA Industrial Average, Dow Jones Industrial, DJI, Dow 30, or simply Dow.\",\"ar\":\"\\u0627\\u0633\\u0645\\u0647 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0643\\u0627\\u0645\\u0644 Dow Jones Industrial Average\\u060c \\u0648 \\u0645\\u0646 \\u0647\\u0646\\u0627 \\u0627\\u062e\\u062a\\u0635\\u0627\\u0631\\u0647 DJIA\\u060c \\u0645\\u0624\\u0634\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062f\\u0627\\u0648 \\u062c\\u0648\\u0646\\u0632 30 \\u0647\\u0648 \\u0645\\u0624\\u0634\\u0631 \\u0623\\u0633\\u0647\\u0645 \\u064a\\u062a\\u0643\\u0648\\u0646 \\u0645\\u0646 30 \\u0634\\u0631\\u0643\\u0629 \\u0623\\u0645\\u0631\\u064a\\u0643\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0643\\u0628\\u0631\\u0649. \\u0648\\u064a\\u0633\\u0645\\u0649 \\u0623\\u064a\\u0636\\u0627\\u064b DJIA Industrial Average \\u0623\\u0648 Dow Jones Industrial \\u0623\\u0648 DJI \\u0623\\u0648 Dow 30 \\u0623\\u0648 \\u0628\\u0628\\u0633\\u0627\\u0637\\u0629 Dow.\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">What is the Dow Jones Index<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Its full name is Dow Jones Industrial Average, hence its abbreviation DJIA, the Dow Jones 30 Index is a stock index of 30 major American companies. It is also called DJIA Industrial Average, Dow Jones Industrial, DJI, Dow 30, or simply Dow.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">It is the oldest indexes witnessed by the stock exchange of the United States of America, dating back to its establishment in 1884 AD, by Charles Dow and Edward Jones, and was published on May 26, 1896, under the name of the Dow Jones Industrial Average, (Dow Jones Industrial Average) . When it was established, the index included 12 diversified companies operating in industrial sectors, such as railway companies, sugar, tobacco, gas, cotton, and oil, and the performance of those industrial companies was often viewed as the main feature indicating the performance of the overall economy and the extent of its strength. And this made the Dow Jones Industrial Average one of the main metrics on which to measure the health of the economy in a broad and general way, and although it is currently developing, as the global economy\\u2019s health has been linked to many additional sectors other than the industrial sector, it is still seen until our time The current refers to the Dow Jones Industrial Average as a major measure of the well-being of the US economy.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">How is the Dow Jones Index calculated?<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The total price of all listed shares is divided by a number that takes into account the divisions of shares and dividends. This results in a weighted average.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">This method of calculation has been criticized due to the fact that firms with higher equity prices have more influence than those with higher market capitalization.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Trade the Dow Jones Index<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The Dow Jones Index can be greatly influenced by many factors. Fluctuations are caused by a number of problems, such as:<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">\\u2022 The performance of companies listed on the index, as shown in the quarterly earnings reports and market news reports.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=