(4, 53, 53, '{\"en\":\"US dollar\",\"ar\":\"\\u0627\\u0644\\u062f\\u0648\\u0644\\u0627\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u0645\\u0631\\u064a\\u0643\\u064a\"}', 'post', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'publish', 0, NULL, NULL, '0f58156e63024155a1d35d60d9019c3f.jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":\"The American economy is the strongest economy in the world, and the United States of America is at the forefront of the world in terms of politics, military, technology and in many different fields. This, of course, had a direct impact on the US dollar, which is currently considered the basis for global trade.\",\"ar\":\"\\u064a\\u0639\\u062a\\u0628\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u0642\\u062a\\u0635\\u0627\\u062f \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0645\\u0631\\u064a\\u0643\\u064a \\u0647\\u0648 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u0642\\u062a\\u0635\\u0627\\u062f \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0642\\u0648\\u0649 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0645\\u0633\\u062a\\u0648\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u060c \\u0643\\u0645\\u0627 \\u0623\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0648\\u0644\\u0627\\u064a\\u0627\\u062a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u062a\\u062d\\u062f\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0645\\u0631\\u064a\\u0643\\u064a\\u0629 \\u062a\\u0623\\u062a\\u064a \\u0641\\u064a \\u0637\\u0644\\u064a\\u0639\\u0629 \\u062f\\u0648\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0635\\u0639\\u064a\\u062f \\u0627\\u0644\\u0633\\u064a\\u0627\\u0633\\u064a \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0633\\u0643\\u0631\\u064a \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u062a\\u0643\\u0646\\u0648\\u0644\\u0648\\u062c\\u064a \\u0648\\u0641\\u064a \\u0639\\u062f\\u064a\\u062f \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u062c\\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u062a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u062e\\u062a\\u0644\\u0641\\u0629. \\u0647\\u0630\\u0627 \\u0628\\u0627\\u0644\\u0637\\u0628\\u0639 \\u0643\\u0627\\u0646 \\u0644\\u0647 \\u062a\\u0623\\u062b\\u064a\\u0631 \\u0645\\u0628\\u0627\\u0634\\u0631 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0639\\u0645\\u0644\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062f\\u0648\\u0644\\u0627\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0645\\u064a\\u0631\\u0643\\u064a \\u0627\\u0644\\u062a\\u064a \\u062a\\u0639\\u062a\\u0628\\u0631 \\u0641\\u064a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0648\\u0642\\u062a \\u0627\\u0644\\u062d\\u0627\\u0644\\u064a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0633\\u0627\\u0633 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0630\\u064a \\u064a\\u062d\\u0643\\u0645 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062a\\u062c\\u0627\\u0631\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u064a\\u0629.\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">$$ Currency US dollar $$<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The American economy is the strongest economy in the world, and the United States of America is at the forefront of the world in terms of politics, military, technology and in many different fields. This, of course, had a direct impact on the US dollar, which is currently considered the basis for global trade.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Today, the US dollar has become a basis for valuing and valuing things instead of gold, and this of course made the dollar the first reserve currency in the world. For this reason also, we find that countries, companies and large entities are trying to maintain amounts of the US dollar, to maintain a kind of balance and stability in all their various operations and activities.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">For financial market traders who work in the field of foreign exchange trading, you can imagine that 80% of the movements in the forex markets are caused by the US dollar, and the remaining 20% \\u200b\\u200bare distributed to the rest of the currencies. Therefore, in order to understand the nature of current and future price movements and trends in the currency markets, \\u201cIt is very important to know the movement of the US dollar and expectations regarding the rise or fall of the price of the dollar.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">What are the reasons for the high and low price of the US dollar?<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">In fact, a group of factors come together through which the US dollar can be analyzed and forecast about its movements, whether it is rising or falling, and these reasons are summarized as follows:<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Interest rates, unemployment rates, wage rates, and inflation rates, in addition to consumer prices, producer prices and GDP are among the most important indicators that must be monitored.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Second: The Federal Reserve and the decisions issued by it<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The decisions issued by the Central Bank are considered one of the most important influences on the dollar exchange rate and its value, as these decisions are the ones that define the country\'s economic policies, so it is important to follow the speeches of the head of the central bank in the first instance, and then the rest of the members to know the nature of the policy that the bank is following at the present time.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">For example, talking about easing or tightening policy or hinting at raising or lowering interest rates, all of this certainly leaves traders with a sufficient impression about the nature of the price trend in the near and distant future, and thus the decision to buy and sell currencies on this basis.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Third: Political factors affect the exchange rate of the US dollar<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Political factors greatly affect the movements of exchange rates, as the state is considered an integrated system in which the various \\u201cpolitical, economic, social, military and security factors\\u201d combine to form the sum of the influences that draw current and future trends.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">One of the most important examples of the effect of politics on exchange rate movements is what happened in the US elections, and the peaceful transfer of power indicates a state of political stability, which resulted in a significant increase in the price of the dollar \\\"by about 300 points\\\" within a few hours.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">On the other hand, countries that do not witness internal conflicts and continuous wars will positively affect the value of their currency, unlike countries that suffer from wars and conflicts where the value of the currency is negatively affected and suffer from large fluctuations in exchange rates.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Fourth: Reports of the Federal Open Market Committee<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The Federal Open Market Committee often includes the president and members of the central bank, and meets a number of times during the year to decide on interest rates. \\\"In the American case, this body meets eight times during the year,\\\" and sets out the guidelines for monetary policy and sets interest rates, which are among the most important causes of the rise and fall of the dollar\'s price. Following up on the decisions of this committee is an important priority for traders.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Fifthly: the prices of stocks, bonds and gold affect the exchange rate of the dollar<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">There is a common matter that there is an inverse relationship between stock prices, bond prices and gold prices compared to the US dollar, for example rises in the stock market result in a decrease in the price of the dollar and vice versa, and this belief applies perfectly to bond prices and gold prices.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">In fact, the relationship between the exchange rate of the dollar and the prices of other financial assets cannot be judged in this way, as the interconnected factors are many. Sometimes this relationship may be correct, but other times it may not be. But surely strong signals can be obtained from these assets to anticipate the current and future trends of the US dollar.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">What is the dollar index?<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">The US dollar index is used to measure the strength and value of the dollar in relation to a number of major currencies. These currencies are \\\"the European euro, the British pound, the Japanese yen, the Canadian dollar, the Swiss franc and the Swedish krona.\\\" This indicator takes the symbol USDX or DXY on global exchanges.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Analysis of the US dollar index and its importance to traders<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">At the end of this article, if there is any advice, it is to start the trading day by analyzing the dollar index, so that you can know the general framework that will govern the nature of trading during the day, because the rest of the currencies and financial instruments are affected by the dollar directly.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">After studying the dollar index and taking a general idea of \\u200b\\u200bits movements during the day, it is possible to anticipate the exchange rate of other financial assets directly related to the value of the dollar, and to make the correct trading decision accordingly.<\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\\\" source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro\\\",=\\\"\\\" arial,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" font-size:=\\\"\\\" 15px;=\\\"\\\" outline:=\\\"\\\" 0px=\\\"\\\" !important;\\\"=\\\"\\\"><font color=\\\"#5b5b60\\\">Trading is not difficult, but a trader must first learn the basics of trading.<\\/font><\\/p>\",\"ar\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: #5b5b60;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #999999; font-family: sky, sans-serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 16px;\\\">\\u064a\\u0639\\u062a\\u0628\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u0642\\u062a\\u0635\\u0627\\u062f \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0645\\u0631\\u064a\\u0643\\u064a \\u0647\\u0648 \\u0627\\u064