\\u0631\\u062c \\u0627\\u0644\\u0628\\u0648\\u0631\\u0635\\u0629 (OTC)\\u061b \\u064a\\u0642\\u0648\\u0645 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0633\\u062a\\u062b\\u0645\\u0631\\u0648\\u0646 \\u0648 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u062a\\u062f\\u0627\\u0648\\u0644\\u0648\\u0646 \\u0628\\u0634\\u0631\\u0627\\u0621 \\u0648 \\u0628\\u064a\\u0639 \\u0623\\u0632\\u0648\\u0627\\u062c \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0645\\u0644\\u0627\\u062a \\u0645\\u0646 \\u062e\\u0644\\u0627\\u0644\\u0647.\\r\\n\\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0645\\u0644\\u0627\\u062a\\u060c \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0646\\u0642\\u064a\\u0636 \\u0645\\u0646 \\u0645\\u0639\\u0638\\u0645 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0635\\u0648\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0627\\u0644\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u062e\\u0631\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0642\\u0627\\u0628\\u0644\\u0629 \\u0644\\u0644\\u062a\\u062f\\u0627\\u0648\\u0644\\u060c \\u0647\\u064a \\u0623\\u062f\\u0648\\u0627\\u062a \\u0625\\u0642\\u062a\\u0635\\u0627\\u062f\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0628\\u0642\\u062f\\u0631 \\u0645\\u0627 \\u0647\\u064a \\u0645\\u0624\\u0634\\u0631\\u0627\\u062a \\u0627\\u0642\\u062a\\u0635\\u0627\\u062f\\u064a\\u0629. \\u0648 \\u0628\\u0639\\u0628\\u0627\\u0631\\u0629 \\u0623\\u062e\\u0631\\u0649\\u060c \\u0625\\u0630\\u0627 \\u0643\\u0627\\u0646\\u062a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0628\\u0644\\u062f\\u0627\\u0646 \\u0647\\u064a \\u0634\\u0631\\u0643\\u0627\\u062a \\u0641\\u0625\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0645\\u0644\\u0627\\u062a \\u0633\\u062a\\u0643\\u0648\\u0646 \\u0623\\u0633\\u0647\\u0645\\u0647\\u0627.\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Forex (also known as the foreign exchange market) is known as the place where currency pairs such as the EURUSD or GBPUSD are exchanged and invest their price movements in the market to make money. The forex market is an over-the-counter (OTC) market; Investors and traders buy and sell currency pairs through it.<\\/p><p>Currencies, in contrast to most other tradable financial assets, are economic tools as much as economic indicators. In other words, if countries were companies then currencies would be their shares.<\\/p><p>The Forex market is the most liquid (as well as the most easily accessible). Therefore, it is the most difficult market to manipulate.<\\/p><p>Forex is the largest financial market in the world, with more than 5.09 trillion USD traded every day. In other words, in one day, more money will be traded in the forex markets than the value of Japan\'s GDP! Of these transactions, $ 254 billion is traded through CFDs and other derivative financial instruments.<\\/p><p>Being the largest and most active financial trading market in the world, it is also the most liquid market in the world, which means that it is easy to participate and trade currencies for new beginners and enter and exit trades. And for the most liquid pairs, they can trade currencies at a very low cost (even as little as 1 pip!). This also means that the forex market is very volatile, which creates many opportunities for traders to profit from positive and negative moves in currency trading.<\\/p><p>Knowing the vocabulary used by investors and Forex brokers will not make you a successful trader, but it is necessary to know this in order to become a trader in the beginning.<\\/p><p>Here are some of the most important forex basics:<\\/p><p>Currency pairs<\\/p><p>Spreads and pips<\\/p><p>Margin<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Leverage<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Contract size \\/ lot<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Trading platforms<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Contracts for difference<\\/p><p>Swap<\\/p><p>Forex Explanation - What are Forex Price Quotes?<\\/p><p>To understand what forex is it is essential to understand how currency pairs work before going any further. For example, let\'s take the EUR \\/ USD pair. The euro is called the base currency (or transactional currency), and the US dollar is the counter currency. It gives us a balance of power between the base currency and the counter currency of the exchange rate.<\\/p><p>When looking at the EURUSD or other currency pairs on the Red Box trading platform, we can see two prices: the Bid price and the Ask price (Buy). Usually it is displayed as: EURUSD 1.1034 \\/ 1.1035. The asking price indicates that we can buy 1 \\u20ac at $ 1.1035.<\\/p><p>What are the most popular Forex pairs?<\\/p><p>The most traded currencies are the Euro (EUR), the US Dollar (USD), the Japanese Yen (JPY), the British Pound (GBP) and the Swiss Franc (CHF). Hence, the most popular currency pairs (also known as the majors) are the ones that are most used. The most traded currencies are: the euro against the US dollar, the British pound against the US dollar, the US dollar against the Japanese yen, and the US dollar against the Swiss franc.<\\/p><p>There are three other currencies that are very frequent in forex trading: the New Zealand dollar (NZD), the Australian dollar (AUD) and the Canadian dollar (CAD). When linked to other currencies in a pair, they are categorized as \\\"crosses\\\": NZDCAD, USDCAD or AUDUSD.<\\/p><p>All currency pairs that include the Russian ruble, the Czech koruna, the Polish zloty, the Hungarian forint, the Swedish krona, or the Norwegian krone are considered \\\"exotic\\\" pairs. They account for only 10% of the currency exchange market.<\\/p><p>What are Forex CFDs?<\\/p><p>If you have ever wondered what Forex is, and have researched teaching currency trading for beginners, you may have seen the term \\u201cForex CFDs\\u201d at some point. There are two ways to trade Forex: using Contracts for Difference (CFD) or Spot Forex (also known as margin). Forex spot involves buying and selling of the actual currency. For example, you can buy a certain amount of sterling against the euro, and then, once the value of the pound increases, you can then exchange the euro for the pound again, and receive more money compared to what you originally spent on the purchase.<\\/p><p>CFD stands for \\\"Contract For Difference\\\", and is a contract used to represent movement in prices of financial instruments. In Forex terms, this means that instead of buying and selling large quantities of currencies, you can take advantage of price movements without owning the asset itself. Along with Forex, CFDs are also available on stocks, indices, bonds, commodities, and cryptocurrencies. In any case, CFDs allow you to trade on the price movements of these instruments without having to purchase them.<\\/p><p>Who trades in the forex market?<\\/p><p>The most important traders and investors of the forex market are:<\\/p><p>Central banks<\\/p><p>Governments<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Private banks<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Hedge fund investors<\\/p><p>\\u2022 ETF investors<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Mediators<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Beginners, professional, and investor traders<\\/p><p>Among all Forex traders, central banks have the greatest influence on forex rates. Indeed, their policies (quantitative easing) and decisions (interest rates) are regulated by the \\\"supply\\\" of the currency and they take responsibility for it.<\\/p><p>What is the Forex Market?<\\/p><p>When it comes to the economy, the bid and ask price drive market prices. This principle also applies to the foreign exchange market.<\\/p><p>When the currency is bought, the demand for it increases, which pushes the price higher. Likewise, every time a currency is sold, the supply increases, causing the price to fall. The effect of each buying and selling process in the Forex market is directly proportional to the transaction size of each transaction.<\\/p><p>Most of the news and economic events started<\\/p>\",\"ar\":\"<p>\\u064a\\u0639\\u0631\\u0641 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0641\\u0648\\u0631\\u0643\\u0633 (\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0639\\u0631\\u0648\\u0641 \\u0623\\u064a\\u0636\\u0627 \\u0628\\u0627\\u0633\\u0645 \\u0633\\u0648\\u0642 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0635\\u0631\\u0641 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u062c\\u0646\\u0628\\u064a) \\u0623\\u0646\\u0647 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0643\\u0627\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0630\\u064a \\u064a\\u062a\\u0645 \\u0641\\u064a\\u0647 \\u062a\\u06